## Proposed Changes

### Phase A — AppContext: Customer Store Context

#### [MODIFY] [AppContext.jsx](file:///c:/Users/praga/.gemini/antigravity-ide/scratch/jewellery-website/src/context/AppContext.jsx)
- Add `customerSelectedStore` state (separate from `currentStore` which is admin-only).
- Persist it to `localStorage` as `jw_customer_store`.
- Expose `customerSelectedStore`, `setCustomerSelectedStore`, `allPublicStores`, and `isCustomerStorePromptOpen` / `setIsCustomerStorePromptOpen` from the context.
- On auth-state-change, when `userData.role === 'customer'`:
  - Fetch all `active` stores from Firestore (public read — no `userStores` required).
  - Store them in `allPublicStores`.
  - If only one store exists, auto-select it.
  - If multiple exist and no store is saved, set `isCustomerStorePromptOpen = true`.
- `addToCart` should tag each cart item with `storeId: customerSelectedStore` so cart is always store-bound.

