## Backward Compatibility

| Scenario | Behavior |
|---|---|
| Customer has no store selected | `createOrder` is called with `null` storeId → no `storeId` stamped (legacy behavior) |
| Customer selects a store | `storeId` stamped on order → flows into store dashboard |
| Admin with no activeStore | Gets global view (no where clause) |
| Super Admin | Always global, `storeId = 'GLOBAL'` passes through |
| Legacy orders without storeId | Still visible to customers in `OrderHistory`; admin global view shows them |

