## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Cart store-locking:** When a customer adds products from Store A, then changes to Store B — should we:
> 1. Clear the cart and start fresh (strict isolation)
> 2. Warn the customer but allow mixed cart (flexible)
> 3. Allow mixed cart and let the first item's store define the order storeId

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **"Shop without selecting a store" option:** Should customers be allowed to skip store selection and shop globally (no storeId on orders)? Or should store selection be mandatory?

> [!NOTE]
> **Product visibility:** When a customer selects Store A, should they see *only* products tagged with `storeId = storeA`, or also products with no `storeId` (legacy global catalog)? Recommend: show both (store-specific + global catalog).

